episodes.title: Cult/Ritual Abuse: It is real
episodes.description:
Cult and ritual abuse is one of the worse memories to experience. In this video I share from my book "Multiple Personality One Woman's Journey from Discovery to Recovery" Part Three, Ritual Abuse, Where do I go from here.
I share several memories from the cult abuse, starting with the first memory which was triggered by a simple family event. Ritual/ Cult abuse is the most difficult memories to experience. They are bazaar, unbelievable, and designed to be so. They create doubt, fear, and disbelief. 
You can work through them, don't give up, there is a light at the end of the tunnel. Trust yourself and trust the alter's memories.

episodes.title: DID Communications
episodes.description:
Dissociative identity disorder (DID) AKA multiple personality disorder (MPD), is a controversial disorder. This is a real disorder, and is curable. The journey is hard especially when dealing with the memories,  but it is worth it. There are false ideas of what DID is or isn't. My goal is to be a positive voice for this serious disorder. In this session I will share some of the communications that took place while working with and through the reality of living with dissociative identity disorder. 
Communications within the DID system is very important to integration. Without communications you can not understand what the different personalities need and how to learn about each one.

episodes.title: Dissociative identity disorder, Journey from discovery to recovery
episodes.description:
In this video, Dr Jackie F shares her journey of dissociative identity disorder (DID)  from discovery to diagnoses. Her personal story takes you from the first memory of abuse to discovering of her first alter (altered personality); a young girl of 5 years old. The strangeness of this disorder is one of the reasons some healthcare professionals do not believe the validity of DID. The journey is difficult, but worth the journey for the positive results of integration that comes at the end.
